Jul 4 2009 	Ideal	Spent three nights here in June. We wanted somewhere central within walking distance of the main attractions and transport in SF. The hotel is at the corner of Bush and Grant, right next to the China Town gate. We stayed in a corner room on the eighth floor. It had two side windows on either side of the bed, as well as the main front window looking onto Bush St. This meant that the room was very bright and airy. The pale green decor was also very welcoming and soothing. It was spotlessly clean - no dust anywhere. One day when we were leaving the room we saw the maid scrubbing the door of another room - now I have never seen that before!The staff were friendly and welcoming and always acknowledged you when you entered and exited the building. They were very helpful when we checked out as we had a few hours to wait before we needed to be at the airport. They held onto our bags and even arranged for a taxi to pick us up from the front door at the exact time we requested it.This is a green hotel and this is evident in a number of ways. There are separate bins for different types of recyclable waste, plus they don't print you a receipt when you check out. It has an ideal location and there are loads of places to eat nearby, as a result of which we never got to sample what the hotel had to offer food-wise.The only negative thing I have to say about the hotel is that our room was near the top, and the rooms above us had an outside patio area. Unfortunately on the last two nights our sleep was disturbed by the inconsiderate guests above us constantly re-arranging the patio furniture until about 3am. The sound of metal scraping against concrete directly above your head is not the best thing for a good nights sleep. This didn't detract from our experience too much though and we would definitely stay here again the next time we're in SF. This is a lovely clean hotel and we highly recommend it.	
