Apr 28 2009	Loved it... great value for SF	You can't beat the location, the friendliness of the staff, and what you get for your dollar, especially for San Francisco. We absolutely loved our experience at this hotel. We booked a standard double/double, and upon check-in were upgraded to a 7th floor deluxe... and a corner room at that! The room was HUGE for the city. Spacious, clean, beautiful -- great flatscreen TV and DVD player, beautiful granite bathroom, ridiculously comfortable beds and linens, and a powerful shower with hot water for days. My only very minor complaint about the room is that the mini-fridge is one of those sensor-type minibars, so you can't store perishable food you might purchase on your own. We stayed for 3 nights, and on our second night, we unfortunately had some obnoxious neighbors... at 11pm they were playing guitar, singing, banging on bongos and burning incense! (I'm an extremely light sleeper, and the room was VERY quiet -- no street noise, and even these loud neighbors were a somewhat muffled noise.) I called the desk, especially because the incense was bothering me... and they took it very seriously. They didn't merely call the room and ask them to be quiet, they sent up a team of security... the noise immediately stopped, as well as the odor. The next day, I checked to see if the same people would be in the room next to me, and they were -- however, the desk told me there had been a note made in the computer about the incense and noise, and that the people had been firmly warned and they would be asked to leave immediately if I had any more problems. As someone who is a frequent business traveler, I'm kind of used to being sometimes blown off by the front desk, but the Orchard Garden took my complaints seriously. The next night, there were no problems whatsoever.The only overall negative is that we really didn't like the hotel's restaurant &quot;Roots.&quot; Food was mediocre, overpriced, not great service. But definitely not a drawback in a city where you have a ton of dining options within walking distance.One other fantastic feature is the free Wireless Internet! I will absolutely stay at this hotel on my next trip to SF.	
