Feb 21 2009 	Like this hotel but...	I have mixed feelings about the Orchard Garden Hotel. My girlfriend and I stayed here in late January, 2009 for her birthday trip. We travel to San Francisco about 4-5 times a year for pleasure. What we liked:1) The location of this hotel is absolutely the best. Chinatown, is right outside the front door. Ferry Building Plaza and Union Square are both easy walks. 2) Plenty of good restaurants are less than a mile away. 3) Great accessibility. To get here from the San Francisco airport, just jump on the BART ($5.35), take it to Montgomery Station and walk up to the hotel. 4) The staff is extremely helpful. They upgraded us after I filed a complaint about my room. 5) Our first room (a Junior Suite), although a bit small, was fine with a nice comfortable bed.What we didn't like:1) We could hear way too much of what was going on in the next door room. We were awakened by the couple next door making love and then literally could hear their pillow talk afterwards. We were very surprised that such a nice new hotel wasn't designed to include adequate sound proofing. This problem was definitely a deal breaker for me and I complained to the front desk the next morning. They were extremely helpful and upgraded us to one of the top floor Terrace Suites which was great. So as I said, I am torn. I really like this hotel. But unfortunately, I am hesitant about going back. My girlfriend, on the other hand, is willing to give them another chance. So, if you stay here, be sure to mention that you want a room that is quiet (especially in the middle of the night).	
