Aug 11 2008 	Great all round experience	I agonized over which hotel to choose for our 10 year anniversary. I finally decided on the Orchard Garden and I don't regret my decision at all. The hotel gets a thumbs up for:* Very clean, well appointed room.* Extremely helpful staff* Great location (close to Union square, Chinatown and North Beach).* It really is a very green hotel. Not just made up stuff to market themselves as green.My only very minor complaints are:* The wireless internet connection was terrible in my room. I had to resort to a wired connection, which worked fine.* While the room was incredibly quiet, I felt like the other room doors banged a little loud at night. It would be great if they could install some kind of quiet close device. Please don't let this put you off. I'm a bit picky about noise issues and the room was very quiet.* The rooms are a touch narrow. This didn't bother me at all, but it might bother some people.The continental breakfast was good, but I wouldn't recommend getting it as part of your room rate. I got a little tired of the continental breakfast after 3 or 4 days, but I didn't want to pay full price for the cooked breakfast when I already had the free continental breakfast. You can always pay for the continental breakfast if you want it and you're not really getting any discount by including it in your room rate.	
