Mar 26 2008 	Great experience staff and room!	We had a wonderful stay at the Orchard Garden Hotel. The rooms were tastefully decorated and spacious. The front desk staff was very helpful and friendly. They provided great restaurant suggestions and travel directions. We also enjoyed the roof top terrace for its views of the city. This hotel is much more energy conscious than other hotels we have stayed at. They take care of their property and the impact that they have on the environment. They offer recycling in the rooms and have energy efficient technology to regulate how much electricity you are using in your room. It may not be 100% organic and green in every single aspect but it came pretty close. Upon speaking to the staff about the hotel, it is apparent that there is great effort taken to be sustainable. It is way ahead of most hotels and it is a LEED building. We greatly enjoyed our stay here because of the great service and the great location. This hotel is a brief 5-10 minute walk to all the shopping near Union Square and it is close to the financial district. We didn't use it, but the hotel offers complimentary town car service to the financial district. It was also a 10 minute walk to the BART station (Montgomery St. Station). The hotel was excellent and we will be staying here again next time we visit in San Francisco.	
Mar 24 2008 	beware	This hotel came highly recommended and we were looking forward to staying in a beautiful green hotel. Upon our arrival, we were quite favorably impressed with the room. Our room was actually large for San Francisco, and it was quite clean and lovely.The first thing that distressed me about the hotel was the fact that other than one Clif bar, I found that none of the mini-bar snacks were organic. We have stayed in green hotels and inns all around the US and Europe, and this lack of organic food was a big surprise to me. The hotel's restaurant also says nothing about organic foods on its menu, although they note that they use sustainable fish and hormone-free meats. We did eat dinner with them anyway and the food was quite delicious, but I was disappointed that it wasn't what I consider really &quot;green.&quot;Now here comes the bad part. When we checked out (after a one night stay) we found out that the parking for one night was $38.00 + $5.32 tax. I live in a city that has very high parking fees, but this seemed excessive. Whatever -- it's just play money on vacation anyway. But we found out, after arriving at the airport, they gave us the wrong car!!!!!!! Another guest had rented an identical car and they gave us his. Our car was still sitting there with a $2000 painting in the back. I called the hotel and spoke to a young man there who seemed to try and put the blame on me (didn't you notice it was the wrong car?). He never apologized, and asked me how I wanted to pay for the shipping of my painting. What? I said I didn't think I should have to pay -- so they shipped it at their cost, but it came damaged because it was packed so carelessly. He told me the manager would call me to let me know that everything was taken care of, but, of course, I never got a call back.There's more. A few days later, I found a charge for over $100 on our credit card. My husband called the hotel and they said they had no record of this charge, but agreed it was incorrect. The charge was supposed to be $43.32 for the (overpriced) parking, and the operations manager said they would refund us the parking fee (since they gave us the wrong car!!).Big mix up. Today I checked the card to make sure they had given us the refund. Oh my. They not only didn't refund us that %100+, they charged us another parking fee! Gee whiz, now they are just dipping into our funds any time they feel like it!So the hotel isn't really so green, they won't apologize to you if something goes wrong, and you should be very wary of giving them your credit card, but otherwise it's very nice.	
