May 17 2007 	great stay at the Orchard Garden	I traveled to San Francisco for the first time in November, 2006, with my 13 year old daughter for a rite of passage trip, just the two of us. Booked our hotel on the internet. After endless searching, the choices were many, made reservations at a different place. Looked some more and luckily decided to make a change and go green. Cancelled our previous hotel and booked in the Orchard Garden. We got a good rate because the hotel was still under construction. My daughter and I arrived after a long day of travel, and the Orchard Garden was to be our &quot;oasis&quot; for our 4 night stay. It was convenient, gracious, serene, very sleek and clean, and all around great! We both slept as well in the hotel beds as we did at home. The bathroom was spacious and nice to use. What I loved most was the air exchange system...no need to feel closed in and stuffy, with windows I couldn't open like in most hotel rooms. The air in the room was fresh and the thermostat system easy to use so we were comfortable in the day and slept cool at night. All the people who worked there were helpful and friendly. My daughter and I felt welcome and safe.I wish we could have experienced the restaurant and rooftop garden, but they weren't done yet. Even with construction work durng the day, our room was perfect. Actually wish we could have had more time to luxuriate in our wonderful room.Walking around town I stopped by the hotel we almost stayed at. It looked nice, but big with lots of hustle and bustle. The Orchard Garden was personable and quiet. I hope to return to San Francisco someday and would love to be able to stay in the Orchard Garden again. I recommend it to anyone.	
May 15 2007 	Gem at the Gates of China Town	After a long flight from HI, we checked in late at the Orchard Garden. The staff was very nice, check in was a breeze. Since we hadn't had dinner yet, we asked if anything was open to serve at 9:30 p.m. Turns out there is a restaurant inside the hotel, called Roots, that was excellent!! The room was very comfortable. The bed just right and perfect for a good nights rest. The honor bar was affordable.The location was the best. The gates to China Town were right next door. We appreciate that the owner of the hotel made this a &quot;green&quot; hotel, specifically for guests with medical problems, using chemical free cleaning products. We loved this hotel and would definitely stay there again!	
May 15 2007 	Green with happiness!	This was a last minute change. We were going to originally stay where our family was at the Stanford Court, but moved here for a better rate. I'm a native to the city, and wanted my visit back home to be less Union Square-y.First, I've stayed at their sister property, The Orchard, and thought that's where I had booked this reservation. I was scared when I realized it wasn't, but my fears were unwarranted. This place is beautiful. All the rooms are green: organic cleaning products, recycle bins, key-card electric, etc. I loved it. The beds are super comfy with plush comforters, flat panel TV's, free wireless, iHome alarm clocks for your iPod, Aveda products...all you can want.I had a small issue at their free breakfast, which consists of fresh baked goods (croissants the size of your foot, seriously), fruit, awesome coffee and sliced meat, and they quickly made it right, sending a lovely bottle of wine to our room. The rooftop patio is a nice place to unwind after walking all day. If you're looking for large rooms, a thousand employees, 34 elevators and groups of tourists blocking the doors, look elsewhere. If you want a good SF experience, in walking distance to Union Square, FiDi, Muni, BART and everything else, check this place out.	
Apr 30 2007 	A Wonderful Find	We just got back from a terrific vacation in San Francisco. The wonderful service and value from the Orchard Garden Hotel added to our vacation experience. The hotel is centrally located, within easy walking distance to China Town, Union Square, shopping, restaurants, and the BART subway system. The hotel is very modern, clean, and has terrific service. We'll be coming back for more.	
Apr 22 2007 	Wonderful family stay	Our family of four recently stayed at the Orchard Garden Hotel April 17-19. After doing extensive research on Trip Adivsor, I booked this hotel as one of our stops during our Spring Break road trip. We had a fabulous stay. Loved this wonderful property. The employees, the service, the cleanliness and the wonderful rooms were all a pleasure. The breakfast worked well for all of us. Something for everyone including two kids. The location was perfect and we could not find fault with a thing. Looking forward to staying at the Orchard Garden Hotel the next time we visit San Francisco!	
Apr 21 2007 	Amazing location totally new affordable price.	I recently came back from a 5 night stay at the hotel during a conference. I specifically looked for a place which was both in walking distance from the Moscone Center, yet still far away from Powell street (and some of its dodgy inhibitants during night).The Orchard Garden was perfectly located on the entrance to China Town, 10 minutes from the conference center, and to my surprise - it was brand new!The room was great, and so was the complimentary WiFi connection and breakfast.I highly recommend this hotel, at least until they realize how low they are priced ($169 a night) compared with similar other places...	
Apr 11 2007 	Great stay at the Orchard Garden!	We just got back tonight from a 4 night stay at the Orchard Garden Hotel. Everything was great! The room and hotel was brand new, so everything was clean and fresh. The staff was very helpful and cooperative. (However, if you are expecting luxury treatments such as staff carrying your luggage for you, etc, don't count on it - we dragged ours up and down by ourselves!) One extra bonus which we really found helpful was the complimentary European buffet breakfast, full of fresh fruit, juices, coffee, homemade scones, muffins, toast, croissants, ham, cheese, etc. The location was fine, near all the shopping at Union Square, and if you are into it, it is right next to the China town gate. They also have complimentary usage of high speed computers for their guests, so you don't have to lug along your laptop. The hotel is brand new and all the kinks have not been worked out. At 4:00am we were awakened by a drill in which we all had to run down the stairs-it turned out to be a false alarm! This was the only major inconvenience since we were on the 8th floor, and had to run down all those stairs, and I have a bad knee. When I complained to the management, they comped us for the night, which was totally unexpected. All in all, we are accustomed to staying in the finest of hotels(usually the major chains), but this suited us just fine. We will definitely stay there again and highly recommend it!!!	
Apr 10 2007	A Gem of a Hotel in San Francisco	We decided to try one of the new, smaller boutique hotels in San Francisco. We usually stay at the larger, chain hotels (read Hyatt). The Orchard Garden hotel on Bush Street is a &quot;green&quot; hotel that we discovered on the internet. We reserved a two-day stay taking advantage of their &quot;Park and Shop&quot; special. It was a great deal for us, since we had a car to get around the City and were not thrilled at the thought of paying $35 per day just for parking. The package included parking and a great European buffet breakfast. The room was compact but very clean, efficient and &quot;green.&quot; We applaud them for their efforts to conserve the environment. The staff was always courteous and accommodating and ready to help with directions, suggestions and such. We enjoyed our stay there and definitely will return.	
Apr 2 2007	Green and Great	They make a big deal of being the first LEEDs hotel in SF. I'm not sure exactly what it means except that the hotel is environmentally friendly. This is just a feel good bonus. The hotel is excellent whether it's green blue or brown. Flat screen Tv's were a nice surprise and some interesting elements such as the sliding bathroom door and the power killing key card. The hotel had that new freshness about it. The restaurant was excellent and the location couldn't be beat. A short and relatively flat walk to shopping. China Town was just around the corner. The front desk staff did a great job of stirring me to a not to tourisy Chineese Restaurant in China Town.	
Mar 22 2007 	Loved the Orchard Garden!!	My husband and I loved the Orchard Garden Hotel and would definitly recommend it!! It was new, very clean, and had a lot to offer for a reasonable price. Great location!! - everything was right outside our door....chinatown, union square shopping, cable cars. We were able to walk to everything. Great breakfast included, with fresh fruits, awesome home made scones, coffee, granola. The staff was very polite. We arrived late at night, very tired, and they immediately came out to get our bags, and valet our car. Check in/check out was fast. Staff offered us directions for our drive home. Very comfortable rooms with flat screen, mini fridge was stocked with everything, very clean spacious bathrooms. Nice Aveda products in bathroom too! The bed was sooo comfortable! We will absolutely stay here again on our next trip to San Fran. Quiet hotel. (The hotel restaurant was good, but pricey and not a huge menu selection.)	
Feb 27 2007	Orchard Garden Hotel not quite Above Average	Newly openned in San Francisco, the Orchard Garden Hotel is really nothing special. It is in an excellent location, right down the street from the gates to Chinatown. I arrived on Superbowl Sunday-no TV in a lounge to watch the game I went and purchased a few things to enjoy the game in my room. I went to stock the empty mini refrigerator only to find it did not work. I did get switched to another room, but only after 45 minutes of haggling. The room they switched me to was smaller. Ok fine, so I watch the game, had a couple of beers. All is ok. I had also purchased some different cheeses I kept in the refigerator as well. I came back to my room day 2 and all of the contents that I had in the refigerator was sitting on the desk! Cheese of course spoiled and beer and soda no longer cold. I expressed my disappointment in how that was handled, only to hear that the vendor they hired to stock the mini refrigerator was responsible and that they were sorry. No offer to compensate for anything.On a positive note, the breakfast in the morning was very enjoyable. Fresh fruit, cereal, rolls, juice and coffee. The customer service I feel was poor.	
Feb 26 2007 	Orchard Garden Hotel is great	I had the pleasure of staying at the Orchard Garden Hotel on February 8, 2007. The Hotel location is excellant - Union Square, shops restaurant and cable cars at your doorstep. Chinatown nearby as well. Rooms are very comfortable with king beds, marble bath and nice bath amenities. Bar and restaurant are top of the line. Excellent cocktails, food was delcious with a large choice on the menu. Best part is the staff who make the perfect combination of professional, courteous and friendly. Included in the rate is breakfast in the cheery dining room. Cold breakfast buffet with something to please everyone. Very important feature of this new Hotel, is it is rated as a green hotel. 95 percent of the building materials are recycled. Was very surprised to learn that the attractive sheer curtains were actually made from recycled plastic bottles ! Stay at a wonderful hotel and help save the planet while you are at it.	
Feb 26 2007	loved this hotel	I stayed one night at this hotel. It is in a great location at the edge of chinatown, between the financial district and union square shopping area in San Francisco. The rooms are very nice, bathrooms are large. Flat screen tv's with DVD players. Beds are very comfortable. They have a business center and small gym.Roots restaurant is excellent. A group of 10 of us ate there and everyone loved their meals.Staff is young, energetic and very nice. I would definately stay here again.	
Feb 19 2007 	Great location clean quiet.	My sweetheart and I just spent last week at the Orchard Garden Hotel. The location is great, and within walking distance to many of the city's tourist sights. Coming from a small, very quiet town I was concerned about the noise level at the hotel. I was very happy about how very quiet the hotel was, even on the eve of Chinese New Year and the firecrackers that were going off. The staff was professional but still very friendly. Breakfast was a bit spotty, get there early as the scones are worth it and the coffee is good (and I am picky about coffee). The room was a bit small, (I would have liked to have 2 sitting chairs) but the good size bathroom made up for it. Everything is new and clean, no old smoke smells. I would recommend it, we already have plans to return.	
